{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/docs/guide/artifacts","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/docs/guide/artifacts"},"id":"98d477d5-e60e-51af-a5bd-04b646a72fa1","html":"<h2 id=\"introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-label=\"introduction permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introduction</h2>\n<p>When a <strong><a href=\"https://onwatchus.github.io/documentation/docs/guide/pipeline\">Pipeline</a></strong> is completed, an \"artifact\" is generated by a series of defined steps.</p>\n<p>The most common strategy is to use <strong>docker images</strong> to be able to display the results with greater security and being sure that the generated <strong>code runs equally in development as in the production environment</strong></p>\n<p>For this projects, the docker images is published on <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ecr/?nc1=h_ls\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>AWS Elastic Container Registry (ECR)</strong></a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/documentation/static/d7533ba2d0b169b9369c3e2ee724d666/78415/ecr-example.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 36.66666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Docker image\"\n        title=\"Docker image\"\n        src=\"/documentation/static/d7533ba2d0b169b9369c3e2ee724d666/c1b63/ecr-example.png\"\n        srcset=\"/documentation/static/d7533ba2d0b169b9369c3e2ee724d666/5a46d/ecr-example.png 300w,\n/documentation/static/d7533ba2d0b169b9369c3e2ee724d666/0a47e/ecr-example.png 600w,\n/documentation/static/d7533ba2d0b169b9369c3e2ee724d666/c1b63/ecr-example.png 1200w,\n/documentation/static/d7533ba2d0b169b9369c3e2ee724d666/78415/ecr-example.png 1207w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>To manage the creation of the repositories in AWS-ECR, we will use <a href=\"https://www.terraform.io/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Terraform</strong></a></p>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"repository-for-infrastructure\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#repository-for-infrastructure\" aria-label=\"repository for infrastructure permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Repository for infrastructure</h3>\n<p>This repo contains the configurations used:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/OnWatchUS/infrastructure/tree/master/01-ecr\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><code>OnWatchUS/infrastructure/tree/master/01-ecr</code></strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>: You user must be part of \"Dev\" Team of github org.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This is the default github action for generate a Docker image:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-yaml\">  build-and-push:\n    name: Create docker image\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    needs: build\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v1\n      - uses: kciter/aws-ecr-action@v1\n        with:\n          access_key_id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}\n          secret_access_key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}\n          account_id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCOUNT_ID }}\n          repo: onwatch/NAME_REPOSITORY\n          region: us-west-2\n          tags: NAME_OR_TAG,${{ github.sha }}\n          create_repo: false\n</code></pre>\n<p>The vars <code>AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID</code>, <code>AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY</code>, <code>AWS_ACCOUNT_ID</code> are required, and the IAM Role requires a ECR permissions.</p>\n<p>The var <code>NAME_OR_TAG</code>, is usually latest, qa.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":null,"title":"Artifacts","sidebar":"Docs","showTitle":true,"hideAnchor":null}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["1006376404","1936182646","3649515864"]}